.TH "funzy_getmemo7" "1" "2026-06-09" "" "funzyto770 User Manuals"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
funzy_getmemo7 - extract a memo7 ROM cartridge from a Thomson TO7 tape
file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]funzy_getmemo7\f[R] \f[I]file.k7\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]funzy_getmemo7\f[R] reads a Thomson TO7 or TO7-70 cassette tape
file (.k7 format) and extracts the memo7 ROM cartridge image from it,
writing a 16384-byte .rom file.
.PP
The cartridge must have been previously saved on the TO7 or TO7-70
computer using the following BASIC command:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
SAVEM\[dq]MEMO7\[dq],0,&H3FFF,0
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
The output file takes the name of the input file with the \f[B].k7\f[R]
extension replaced by \f[B].rom\f[R].
.PP
A memo7 ROM cartridge holds 16384 bytes (address range
0x0000\[en]0x3FFF).
Multiple cartridges can be used with the \f[B]funzyto770\f[R] emulator
by placing them in its \f[B]memo7/\f[R] directory.
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
This program accepts no options.
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[I]file.k7\f[R]
Input cassette tape file.
.TP
\f[I]file.rom\f[R]
Output ROM cartridge image (16384 bytes), named after the input file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Extract a memo7 cartridge from a tape recording:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
funzy_getmemo7 memo7.k7
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
The file \f[B]memo7.rom\f[R] is created in the current directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]funzy_getrom\f[R](1), \f[B]funzy_wav2k7\f[R](1)
.SH BUGS
.PP
No known bugs.
